From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: tsf-sync contributors <tsf-sync@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Tue, 1 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: rtw88: add PTP hardware clock for TSF synchronization

Register a PTP hardware clock (/dev/ptpN) for each rtw88 device,
exposing the 802.11 TSF timer to the Linux PTP subsystem.  This enables
phc2sys to synchronize TSF counters across co-located Realtek 802.11ac
radios.

PTP clock operations use direct register access:
  gettime64  -> rtw_read32(REG_TSFTR_LOW) + rtw_read32(REG_TSFTR_HIGH)
  settime64  -> rtw_write32 to both registers
  adjtime    -> read-modify-write
  adjfine    -> no-op (fixed crystal)

The rtw88 driver lacks a REG_TSFTR define, so the TSF register offsets
(0x0560 low, 0x0564 high) are defined locally in ptp.c.

Covers: RTL8822BE/CE, RTL8723DE, RTL8821CE.

Signed-off-by: tsf-sync contributors <tsf-sync@users.noreply.github.com>
---
 6 files changed, 177 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtw88/ptp.c
 create mode 100644 drivers/net/wireless/realtek/rtw88/ptp.h

